				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing PoJ<a name="18546"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 2 04 4:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Trial of flame.
<br />

<br />
This is how I did it.
<br />

<br />
No buffs up, had the following songs memmed.
<br />
1.  Psalm of Veeshan
<br />
2.  Druzzil's Disillusionment
<br />
3.  Chorus of Marr
<br />
4.  Aria of Ascetism
<br />
5.  Tuyen's Chant of Plague
<br />
6.  Tuyen's Chant of Venom
<br />
7.  Filler
<br />
8.  Filler
<br />

<br />
I did this with my wife's cleric.
<br />

<br />
Basically I would go into the trial with Psalm of Veeshan on, and no buffs.  Usually this would be enough to resist the AE (flame based AE that goes off three times and if it sticks have a pretty decent DOT).  The reason for no buffs is that if the AE stuck I would just pulse Disillusionment and wipe it out.
<br />

<br />
Now after the first AE the room would spawn with 4 spawns.  Either the fungoids, fire elementals or a mix of both.  I forget the names of the named of hand, but I would just use to track to see if they were up.  There are two named one being a shaman and the other being a SK, with their respective abilities.
<br />

<br />
Now the thing about this trial is that once you get out of a set range of the MOB it will path to the center of the room and just hang out for a minute or two before it despawns.  Also when not in range it will super regen its hitpoints.  So basically what you have to do is keep it just outside of melee range and this is best accomplished by running backwards, I do it this way because I play most often in 1st person, but you can also switch to third person and click on walk and walk forwards.
<br />

<br />
Now with the MOB agro'd you just use the aforementioned dots and walk around the perimeter of the room.  You only have to watch that it doesn't stop to cast and you get out of range, thus having the MOB super regen. 
<br />

<br />
Its really that simple.  I just brought the cleric along so that I could do it at whatever rate I wanted.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
