				<td colspan="2"><span>You can swarm kite trial of Exectution the first round then
<br />
hop out and start it again.
<br />

<br />
Trial of flame is solo'able by us. It's just much harder.  Pop in
<br />
the trials while Maxing out FR and keeping your first buff slot
<br />
open so you can dispell dots and such.  If you see a named
<br />
debuff it and mez it in place until the rest have despawned
<br />
and you survived the AE dots.  You have to stay within like
<br />
15 feet of the named or he'll run to the center and start his
<br />
1 min countdown.  You know you've accidenally started the
<br />
timer if you see the named hit the pole in the middle and
<br />
you see a message like &quot;flame shoot up from the fire&quot; or
<br />
something to that extent.
<br />

<br />
When you kite the named just turn off your selo and run
<br />
backwards around the outer edge of the trial.  Make sure to
<br />
not go too far from the mob or he heals and runs towards the
<br />
center. Just dot kite them down.  If you get a dot on you,
<br />
just dispell it.  While the named can spawn often, the good
<br />
loots are definatly rare.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
