				<td colspan="2"><span>I just made a post about this on the 60-65 section here at EQDiva.  The point isn't to solo the entire trial but to just pop in see if a named is up and take him down since he can drop a dropable FT1 mask, so you can make some quick pp in the bazaar.  There is some extensive information on soloing the trial of flame on the Concert Hall message board under the topic Hall of Fame, it's around the 3rd or 4th post right now.  And just because the guy duos it with his wife's cleric doesn't mean it isn't soloable by a bard, I've soloed it successfully several times, but have also died several times.  Eventhough it may be eaiser to duo it if you have the luxury of a bot cleric it is still very doable and I'm sure that better bards out there than myself have trivialized this event already.  As soon as I figure everything out I think I should be able to solo it anytime I want, not ever die again and hopefully get some nice loot to make pp in the process.
